      <h2>Results &amp; Product Status</h2>
      <p>I pursued the product independently after leaving Fresh Tilled Soil, developing customers in the wine industry and expanding on the prototype before sidelining the project due to a slow sales cycle and lack of market interest.</p>
      <p>The wine industry is just beginning to get the hang of email marketing, and is a long way from adopting VR as a marketing strategy. Although interested, no interviewees accepted the idea that a VR experience would convert into case sales. They didn't have the language to conceptualize VR experiences.</p>
      <p>Maybe with more user testing and consumer data an argument could be made on numbers alone, but currently, WineVR is too far ahead of the market to be viable.</p>
      <p>Obviously, VR is applicable to many markets, but not all of these are technically mature enough to adopt. Despite the hype, VR hasn't yet claimed a foothold on the fringes of the mainstream outside of gaming.</p>
